{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSExpression","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSExpression"},{"text":" * ","kind":"text"},{"text":"hillshadeMethod","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default value of this property is an expression that evaluates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"type":"text","text":". Set this property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" to reset it to the default value."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethod"},{"type":"text","text":" values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Any of the following constant string values:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"type":"text","text":": The legacy hillshade method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"basic"},{"type":"text","text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"text":" default algorithm.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combined"},{"text":": Hillshade algorithm whose intensity scales with slope. Similar","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-combined"},{"text":" option.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"igor"},{"text":": Hillshade algorithm which tries to minimize effects on other map","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"features beneath. Similar to GDAL’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-igor"},{"text":" option.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"multidirectional"},{"text":": Hillshade with multiple illumination directions. Uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the basic hillshade model with multiple independent light sources.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Predefined functions, including mathematical and string operators","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Conditional expressions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Variable assignments and references to assigned variables","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Step functions applied to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"text":" variable","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This property does not support applying interpolation functions to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"text":" variable or applying interpolation or step functions to feature","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"attributes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The hillshade algorithm to use, one of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodStandard"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodBasic"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodCombined"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodIgor"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethodMultidirectional"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnhillshadestylelayer\/hillshademethod"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer\/hillshadeMethod"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNHillshadeStyleLayer(py)hillshadeMethod","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"hillshadeMethod","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"hillshadeMethod","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"hillshadeMethod"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnhillshadestylelayer","title":"MLNHillshadeStyleLayer","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a style layer that renders raster "},{"type":"text","text":"digital elevation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"model"},{"type":"text","text":" (DEM) tiles on the map."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNHillshadeStyleLayer"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"d